    <!-- Key Principles Section -->
    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> Key Principles of Vastu Shastra</h2>
        <div class="section-content">
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>The Five Elements:</strong> Vastu Shastra is based on the concept of five elements (Earth, Water, Fire, Air, and Space), which must be in balance for a harmonious space.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Cosmic Energy (Prana):</strong> The idea that cosmic energy flows through the building, affecting the well-being of its inhabitants.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Vastu Purusha Mandala:</strong> A sacred diagram used to design spaces in accordance with the flow of energy.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Importance of Directions:</strong> Different directions correspond to specific elements and energies, influencing different aspects of life.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Room Placement Guidelines -->
    <section>
        <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-home"></i> Room Placement According to Vastu</h2>
        <div class="section-content">
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Living Room:</strong> Place in the North or East to promote positive energy flow and social harmony.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Kitchen:</strong> The kitchen should be in the South-East corner to align with the Fire element.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Bedroom:</strong> The ideal location for a bedroom is the South-West corner, promoting stability and health.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Bathroom:</strong> Bathrooms should be in the West or North-West directions to avoid blocking positive energy.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Pooja Room (Prayer Room):</strong> The North-East direction is ideal for spiritual activities.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Importance of Directions -->
    <section>
        <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-compass"></i> Importance of Directions</h2>
        <div class="section-content">
            <p>Each direction has its own significance in Vastu Shastra, influencing various aspects of life:</p>
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>North:</strong> Governed by Kubera (god of wealth), this direction is favorable for prosperity and financial growth.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>South:</strong> Linked to Yama (god of death), South is typically avoided for essential areas like the main entrance or living room.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>East:</strong> Associated with the rising sun, this direction brings new opportunities, good health, and success.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>West:</strong> Represents rest and relaxation, suitable for bedrooms or storage areas.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

